A car smashed through a wall in Polokwane on Saturday morning after the driver took the wrong entrance into town, Limpopo traffic police said. The accident occurred at Zanas next to the N1 as one enters town from Mokopane. The driver used the wrong entrance, the department said on the Arrive Alive website. This is the second vehicle going through a wall in the last four hours in Polokwane. The previous accident was at Lawton and Grobler [streets] [the] driver ran away and left three injured passengers, the brief statement said.